S T A T E O F R H O D E I S L A N D
IN GENERAL ASSEMBLY
JANUARY SESSION, A.D. 2025
____________
H O U S E R E S O L U T I O N
CELEBRATING THE 250TH BIRTHDAY OF THE U.S. ARMY
Introduced By: Representatives Azzinaro, Shekarchi, Blazejewski, Abney, Chippendale,
Kennedy, Paplauskas, Santucci, Hopkins, and Casimiro
Date Introduced: June 10, 2025
Referred To: House read and passed
1 WHEREAS, Since its official birth on June 14, 1775, over a year before the Declaration
2 of Independence was written, the United States Army has played a vital role in the growth and
3 development of the American nation; and
4 WHEREAS, The nature of the Army’s missions have varied depending on the nation’s
5 needs at a particular time, whether fighting a war for survival, developing a transportation
6 network and skilled engineers to support it, providing disaster relief, keeping the peace, or
7 supporting American diplomacy; and
8 WHEREAS, From the first battles at Lexington and Concord to the streets of Mosul and
9 Kandahar, soldiers have always defended freedom and epitomized what is best about America;
10 and
11 WHEREAS, Throughout our nation’s history, generations of brave men and women in
12 the U.S. Army have served with a deep commitment to America’s core values and beliefs, with
13 many making the ultimate sacrifice, giving their lives so that we all would remain free; and
14 WHEREAS, The brave soldiers of the U.S. Army remain "Army Strong," the clearest
15 symbol of America’s commitment to freedom and the country’s preeminent leadership
16 experience, going beyond physical endurance and mental preparedness while encompassing an
17 indomitable spirit, and high ethical and moral values; now, therefore be it
18 RESOLVED, That this House of Representatives of the State of Rhode Island hereby
19 congratulates the U.S. Army on the celebration of its 250th Birthday and honors the servicemen
20 and women who together make it the strength of our nation; and be it further

1 RESOLVED, That the Secretary of State be and he hereby is authorized and directed to
2 transmit a duly certified copy of this resolution to Daniel P. Driscoll, Secretary of the U.S. Army.
